

---

# ðŸš€ **All Docker Commands for Deployment (With Uses)**

## ðŸ”¹ **1. Docker Installation & Version**

| Command                   | Use                              |
| ------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| `docker --version`        | Check Docker version             |
| `docker info`             | Check system-wide Docker details |
| `systemctl start docker`  | Start Docker service             |
| `systemctl enable docker` | Enable Docker at boot            |

---

# ðŸ”¹ **2. Docker Image Commands**

| Command                          | Use                            |
| -------------------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| `docker pull <image>`            | Download image from Docker Hub |
| `docker images`                  | List images                    |
| `docker rmi <image>`             | Remove image                   |
| `docker build -t <image_name> .` | Build image from Dockerfile    |
| `docker tag <src> <dest>`        | Tag an image                   |
| `docker history <image>`         | Show layers of an image        |

---

# ðŸ”¹ **3. Docker Container Commands**

| Command                                | Use                            |
| -------------------------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| `docker run <image>`                   | Run a container                |
| `docker run -d <image>`                | Run container in background    |
| `docker run -p 80:80 <image>`          | Map ports container:host       |
| `docker run -v host:container <image>` | Mount volume                   |
| `docker run -e KEY=VALUE <image>`      | Pass environment variables     |
| `docker run --name myapp <image>`      | Run with custom container name |
| `docker ps`                            | List running containers        |
| `docker ps -a`                         | List all containers            |
| `docker stop <container>`              | Stop container                 |
| `docker start <container>`             | Start container                |
| `docker restart <container>`           | Restart container              |
| `docker kill <container>`              | Force stop                     |
| `docker rm <container>`                | Remove container               |

---

# ðŸ”¹ **4. Docker Logs & Debugging**

| Command                            | Use                           |
| ---------------------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| `docker logs <container>`          | View logs                     |
| `docker logs -f <container>`       | Live logs (follow)            |
| `docker exec -it <container> bash` | Go inside a running container |
| `docker inspect <container>`       | Detailed container info       |
| `docker stats`                     | Live CPU/memory usage         |

---

# ðŸ”¹ **5. Docker Volume Commands**

| Command                       | Use            |
| ----------------------------- | -------------- |
| `docker volume create myvol`  | Create volume  |
| `docker volume ls`            | List volumes   |
| `docker volume inspect myvol` | Inspect volume |
| `docker volume rm myvol`      | Delete volume  |

---

# ðŸ”¹ **6. Docker Network Commands**

| Command                                        | Use                          |
| ---------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| `docker network ls`                            | List networks                |
| `docker network create mynetwork`              | Create custom bridge network |
| `docker network connect mynetwork <container>` | Attach container to network  |
| `docker network inspect mynetwork`             | Inspect network              |

---

# ðŸ”¹ **7. Docker Compose Commands (Deployment Use)**

| Command                         | Use                          |
| ------------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| `docker compose up`             | Start all services           |
| `docker compose up -d`          | Start in background          |
| `docker compose down`           | Stop & remove all containers |
| `docker compose down --volumes` | Remove volumes also          |
| `docker compose logs`           | View logs                    |
| `docker compose restart`        | Restart services             |
| `docker compose build`          | Rebuild services             |
| `docker compose pull`           | Pull all images              |

---

# ðŸ”¹ **8. Docker Deployment-Specific Commands**

## **ðŸ‘‰ 1. Deploy image to remote server**

```
docker save myapp:latest > myapp.tar
scp myapp.tar user@server:/tmp/
docker load < myapp.tar
```

## **ðŸ‘‰ 2. Deploy using Docker Hub**

```
docker login
docker tag myapp username/myapp:v1
docker push username/myapp:v1
```

## **ðŸ‘‰ 3. Deploy using Compose**

```
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d --build
```

---

# ðŸ”¹ **9. Docker Cleanup Commands**

| Command                  | Use                                        |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------------------------ |
| `docker system prune`    | Remove unused containers, images, networks |
| `docker system prune -a` | Remove everything unused                   |
| `docker image prune`     | Remove unused images                       |
| `docker container prune` | Remove stopped containers                  |

---

# ðŸ”¹ **10. Docker Swarm Commands (Advanced Deployment)**

| Command                                             | Use                  |
| --------------------------------------------------- | -------------------- |
| `docker swarm init`                                 | Enable Swarm mode    |
| `docker node ls`                                    | List nodes           |
| `docker stack deploy -c docker-compose.yml mystack` | Deploy stack         |
| `docker service ls`                                 | List services        |
| `docker service ps myservice`                       | Check service status |
| `docker service update --image newimage myservice`  | Rolling update       |

---
